    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6">

                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="assets/images/how-it-works/blockchain.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="features-img">
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">

                <div class="feature-detail">
                    <h1 class="title animated fadeInRight wow">Blockchain</h1>
                    <p class="features-txt animated fadeInRight wow">The only technology which guarantees the storage of your transactional data in an immutable manner. All data is recorded as transactions and grouped in blocks. These go one by one in a linear manner, forming a chain of blocks. Because of links to previous blocks and cryptography algorithms previously added information cannot be changed. The usage of Merkle trees provides auditability and accountability of blockchains. Thus, a user can verify inclusion of his transaction into a blockchain by asking for proof, which can be done without disclosing information on other transactions. Exonum can operate as either a private or permissioned public blockchain.</p>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6 visible-xs-block">

                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="assets/images/how-it-works/bft.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="features-img">
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">

                <div class="feature-detail">
                    <h1 class="title animated fadeInLeft wow">BFT consensus algorithm</h1>
                    <p class="features-txt animated fadeInLeft wow">Byzantine fault tolerant algorithms acknowledge that some actors may behave incorrectly (because of either intentional or unintentional changes). They guarantee the system will operate correctly during maintenance periods or even if under attack. BFT consensus algorithms provide high throughput and transaction settlement usually in under several seconds.</p>
                    <h4 class="animated fadeInLeft wow">Benchmarks demonstrate up to 3500 tps per one core and 2.5 sec transaction settlement time.</h4>
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 hidden-xs">

                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="assets/images/how-it-works/bft.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="features-img">
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
